      • commitTransaction

        public void commitTransaction()
        All changes that have been made to the managed entities in the persistence context are applied to the database and committed.

      • rollbackTransaction

        public void rollbackTransaction()
        The persistence context is cleared of all managed entities, rolling back all pending changes in the persistence tier.

      • isTransactionDirty

        public boolean isTransactionDirty()
        There is currently no way to ask the EntityManager whether changes are pending in the persistence context. For now, we just always assume there are pending changes whenever the EntityManager is active.
        Returns:
        true if the EntityManager is open for business.
